    <h2>European regulations for practical instructors</h2>

    <p>While <strong>ICAO</strong> Annex 1 <strong>does not</strong> detail
        training and experience requirements or recommended practices on how the
        training of on-the-job training instructors should be carried out,
        <strong>Europe Regulation</strong> (EU) 2015/340 <strong>does</strong>
        exactly that.
      </p>

    <p>Another <strong>difference</strong> between the ICAO and EU approaches
        is that ICAO is focused on OJTIs and operational (live) training only,
        whereas in the EU, the Basic regulation uses the generic term
        “instructor on practical skills” and in the <strong>more
          detailed</strong> ATCO Licensing regulation introduces the
        requirements for both OJTIs and Synthetic Training Device Instructors
        (STDIs).</p>

    <p>So, what are these requirements? Take a look at the video for an
        overview of the different requirements that apply to practical
        instructors in the EU.</p>

  </div>

  <div class="ians-column-wide-3">

    {% vimeo 601735281 %}

  </div>

