  <div class="ians-column">

    <h3>
      Privileges
    </h3>

    <p>Once an ATCO has obtained either an OJTI or STDI endorsement, what types
        of training are they allowed to provide (i.e. what are the privileges of the endorsement)?</p>

    <p>An OJTI can provide all types of training (live and simulated). Take a
        look at the <strong>definition of OJTI endorsement</strong> from the
        ATCO Licensing regulation:</p>

    <blockquote>on-the-job training instructor (OJTI) endorsement’ means the
        authorisation entered on and forming part of a licence, indicating the
        competence of the holder to give on-the-job training instruction and
        instruction on synthetic training devices</blockquote>

    <p>However, an STDI <strong>may not</strong> provide operational (OJT)
        training or pre-OJT if the relevant unit endorsement was not held in the
        past.</p>

  </div>

